articles.author: ERIC TUCKER, JIM MUSTIAN, KEVIN McGILL and JACK BROOK
articles.description: NEW ORLEANS (AP) — The Army veteran who drove a pickup truck into a crowd of New Year’s revelers in New Orleans acted alone, the FBI said Thursday, reversing its position from a day earlier that he likely worked with others in the deadly attack that officials said was inspired by the Islamic State group.
articles.title: FBI says driver in New Orleans rampage acted alone, was '100%' inspired by Islamic State group

articles.description: NEW ORLEANS (AP) — The FBI now says the New Orleans truck attacker acted alone in an “act of terrorism” when he drove a pickup truck into a crowd of New Year’s revelers early Wednesday, killing 14 people.
articles.title: The Latest: The FBI now says the New Orleans truck attacker acted alone in an 'act of terrorism'

articles.author: TARA COPP, ALANNA DURKIN RICHER, COLLEEN LONG and TY ONEIL
articles.description: LAS VEGAS (AP) — The highly decorated Army soldier inside a Tesla Cybertruck packed with fireworks that exploded outside Trump International Hotel in Las Vegas shot himself in the head just before detonation, authorities said Thursday.
articles.title: Soldier shot self in head before Cybertruck exploded outside Trump's Las Vegas hotel, officials say

articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — Two deadly incidents on New Year's Day — an attack being investigated as an act of terrorism in New Orleans and an explosion of a Tesla Cybertruck in Las Vegas — both involved vehicles that were rented on Turo, a peer-to-peer car sharing company.
articles.title: Turo-rented cars were involved in 2 deadly incidents this New Year's. Here's what we know

articles.author: KIM TONG-HYUNG
articles.description: SEOUL, South Korea (AP) — South Korea’s anti-corruption agency on Friday dispatched investigators to execute a warrant to detain impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol over his short-lived martial law decree last month, as hundreds of his supporters gathered at his residence in Seoul, vowing to block their approach.
articles.title: South Korean investigators head to Seoul in attempt to detain impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol

articles.author: BRIAN MELLEY
articles.description: LONDON (AP) — A worker digging up clay in a southern England limestone quarry noticed unusual bumps that led to the discovery of a “dinosaur highway” and nearly 200 tracks that date back 166 million years, researchers said Thursday.
articles.title: 'Dinosaur highway' tracks dating back 166 million years are discovered in England

articles.author: JENNIFER PELTZ
articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — Say hello to the latest dog in the American Kennel Club's lineup of recognized breeds.
articles.title: Meet the Danish-Swedish farmdog, the newest breed in the American Kennel Club's lineup

articles.author: BRETT MARTEL
articles.description: NEW ORLEANS (AP) — Ticketed fans in Georgia and Notre Dame gear packed a plaza adjacent to the Superdome, enjoyed music under clear skies — and under the watch of snipers on rooftops — before filtering into the stadium for Thursday afternoon's College Football Playoff quarterfinal at the Sugar Bowl.
articles.title: Superdome re-opens from lockdown for the Sugar Bowl CFP quarterfinal between Georgia and Notre Dame

articles.author: DÁNICA COTO
articles.description: SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) — Jenniffer González Colón was sworn in Thursday as Puerto Rico’s new governor during a normally ebullient ceremony held amid widespread anger over a blackout that hit the U.S.
articles.title: Puerto Rico's new governor sworn in days after a major blackout left much of the island in the dark

articles.author: TOM KRISHER and BERNARD CONDON
articles.description: DETROIT (AP) — Tesla posted its first annual sales drop in more than a dozen years Thursday, undercutting a stock that has soared since Donald Trump’s victory on optimism Elon Musk’s close relationship to the president-elect will help the company.
articles.title: Tesla sales dropped 1.1% in 2024, its first annual decline in a dozen years
